SIMPLE: ghastly
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ghastly
<hw>Ghast"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Ghastlier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>superl.</pos> <adjf>Ghastliest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>gastlich</ets>, <ets>gastli</ets>, fearful, causing fear, fr.
<ets>gasten</ets> to terrify, AS. <ets>g⟦ae⟧stan</ets>. Cf.
<er>Aghast</er>, <er>Gast</er>, <er>Gaze</er>, <er>Ghostly</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Like a ghost in appearance; deathlike; pale; pallid;
dismal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Each turned his face with a <qex>ghastly</qex> pang.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His face was so <qex>ghastly</qex> that it could scarcely be
recognized.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Horrible; shocking; dreadful; hideous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mangled with <qex>ghastly</qex> wounds through plate and mail.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ghastly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ghastly
<hw>Ghast"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a ghastly manner;
hideously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Staring full <qex>ghastly</qex> like a strangled man.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ghastness</ent>⟦br⟧
